race.comment: POLYVANOVA (6) sat on the speed and was too good first-up at Toodyay, winning by 0.2L. She's likely to be prominent from the barrier once again under Watson and she'll have come on from the fresh performance. Will be hard to run down once again. QUEEN'S SACRIFICE (7) wasn't beaten far at Toodyay first-up when sitting on the speed and is expected to be better over this sort of distance. She'll be up front from the inside barrier and with the senior jockey hopping on board, she'll be hard to hold out. FOREVER DREAMING (1) has claims off a much-improved effort last time out. RANDOM REWARDS (10) looks well placed back to this level today following a run in Saturday company last time out. Can put her best foot forward.
